-- China shares find July their best month since December 2012
-- By Grace Li
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 03:09AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 31 (Reuters) - China shares finished their best month since 2012 on a positive note on Thursday, with banks and mining companies leading index solid gains.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended a choppy session up 0.9 percent at 2,201.56 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings rose 1.2 percent. The indexes jumped 7.5 and 8.6 percent, respectively, during July, the best month since December 2012. July's gains let the two mainland indexes move into positive territory for 2014. Inner Mongolia Yili Industrial Group <600887.SS> climbed 5 percent on Thursday to its highest close this year, after media reports said its chairman and three other executives bought more than 40 million shares in the secondary market on Tuesday and Wednesday. Zijin Mining Group <601899.SS> surged 7.1 percent and Zhongjin Gold Corp <600489.SS> 9 percent.